    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In bookbinding, method of holding pages of a book together with glue, using no stitching or sewing. The back of the volume is trimmed to produce a block of separate leaves, the back edges are roughened, adhesive is applied, and the case is attached.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
